title: Ariana Grande Unveils New Snippet of 'Focus'
text:
Comments The singer shares an Instagram clip featuring her belting out some lines from her new single, which will finally arrive in full on October 30. 
Another preview of Ariana Grande 's "Focus" has landed online a little over a week before the single's officially released. On Wednesday, October 21, the 22-year-old songbird shared on Instagram a clip of her performing the song a capella. The 15-second audio highlights Grande's incredible pipes as she belts out, "I know you're hoping that I'll react/ I know you're hopin I'm lookin back/ But if my real ain't real enough... then I dunno what is." A video posted by Ariana Grande (@arianagrande) on Oct 21, 2015 at 9:36am PDT "Focus" will finally come out on October 30 as the first single off Grande's " Moonlight " album. Earlier this week, she previewed what appeared to be the finished version of the track in an ad for her fragrance, "Ari by Ariana Grande". "When I say focus on me I'm not asking to be the center of attention. I'm not asking you to focus on my clothes or my face or my body or my singing voice," the " Scream Queens " star recently explained the song. "By focus on me I literally mean focus on me, on what I'm all about, on what I believe in."
